Figs. 2A and 2B a schematic illustration of the vision mixer shown in Fig. 1;
Figs. 3A to 3C application examples of a vision mixer in a live TV production;
Fig. 4 a schematic block diagram of the system for video processing according to the present invention;
Fig. 5 the block diagram of Fig. 4 in greater detail; and
Fig. 6 the block diagram of Fig. 4 in greater detail according to an alternative embodiment.

claim.claim-text:
Method of processing video and/or audio signals utilizing a control unit and a plurality of processing units (401, 403, 405, 407), which are communicatively connected for exchanging digital data in a packetized format, wherein the method comprises the following steps:
- receiving video signals at the processing units (401, 403, 405);
- sending video signals from the processing units (401, 403, 405);
- sending command signals (A, B, C) from the control unit (407) to one or several processing units (401, 403, 405);
- scheduling the execution of command signals received in the processing units (401, 403, 405) to compensate for signal latencies caused by the communication of signals between the control unit (407) and one processing unit and/or between two processing units and for compensating latencies caused by the processing of signals in the processing unit(s) (401, 403, 405).

Method of processing video and/or audio signals utilizing a control unit and a plurality of processing units (401, 403, 405, 407), which are communicatively connected for exchanging digital data in a packetized format, wherein the method comprises the following steps:
- receiving video signals at the processing units (401, 403, 405);
- sending video signals from the processing units (401, 403, 405);
- sending command signals (A, B, C) from the control unit (407) to one or several processing units (401, 403, 405);
- executing command signals (A, B, C) in the processing units without delay but only after each processing unit (401, 403, 405) has received all necessary input signals for performing the processing.
